 :tx/rationale "THE FINAL LOOP: Ontology discovery. The calibration loop learns weights. Boundary discovery learns structure. But neither learns the ontology — what categories of knowledge exist. The missing loop: cluster observations by attribute patterns, detect recurring structures that dont match any declared claim type, propose new categories. Example: 12 observations all reference file paths with confidence over 0.8 and led to task creation — thats implementation insights, a category the policy doesnt have. The system proposes: I detected a recurring pattern. Should I create a new claim type? This closes the ontology loop: policy defines categories, usage reveals new categories, policy evolves. The systems theory of knowledge becomes more complete through use. All three loops closed: weight calibration (OBSERVER-4), structure discovery (OBSERVER-5), ontology discovery (OBSERVER-6)."
